Package: bayescoveragemodel
Title: Bayesian Transition Models for Estimating and Forecasting Health Coverage Indicators
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Leontine", "Alkema", , "lalkema@umass.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Shauna", "Mooney", role = "aut"),
    person("Sophia", "Kagoye", role = "ctb"),
    person("Leonardo", "Ferreira", role = "ctb"),
    person("Roland", "Mady", role = "ctb"),
    person("Countdown BayesCoverage Team", role = "ctb")
    )
Description: Fits Bayesian hierarchical transition models to health coverage
    indicators (e.g., ANC4, institutional delivery) using survey and routine
    data. Implements models using Stan for Bayesian inference, with support for
    global and local (country-specific) model fitting, out-of-sample validation,
    and subnational estimation.
